questions.question: Given that x varies from 2 to 5 (i.e x1 to x2) and $$ Y(x) = x^3 - 5x + 3 $$ find the integration of Y using Guass quadrature method for 3 points.
Given that x varies from 1 to 4 (i.e x1 to x2) and $$ Y(x) = 2x^2 + 1 $$ find the integration of Y using Guass quadrature method for 3 points.
